#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Chaḷabhijātisutta"
msgstr "57. The Six Classes of Rebirth"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "an6.57:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

# “Classes” alone does not capture the sense of abhijati, i.e. rebirth into a class.
msgctxt "an6.57:1.3"
msgid "“pūraṇena, bhante, kassapena chaḷabhijātiyo paññattā—"
msgstr "“Sir, Pūraṇa Kassapa describes six classes of rebirth:"

msgctxt "an6.57:1.4"
msgid ""
"kaṇhābhijāti paññattā, nīlābhijāti paññattā, lohitābhijāti paññattā, "
"haliddābhijāti paññattā, sukkābhijāti paññattā, paramasukkābhijāti paññattā."
msgstr "black, blue, red, yellow, white, and ultimate white."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena kaṇhābhijāti paññattā, orabbhikā "
"sūkarikā sākuṇikā māgavikā luddā macchaghātakā corā coraghātakā "
"bandhanāgārikā ye vā panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā. (1)"
msgstr ""
"The black class of rebirth consists of slaughterers of sheep, pigs, poultry, "
"or deer, hunters or fishers, bandits, executioners, butchers of cattle, "
"jailers, and any others with a cruel livelihood."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena nīlābhijāti paññattā, bhikkhū "
"kaṇṭakavuttikā ye vā panaññepi keci kammavādā kriyavādā. (2)"
msgstr ""
"The blue class of rebirth consists of mendicants who live on thorns, and any "
"others who teach the efficacy of deeds and action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.384"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena lohitābhijāti paññattā, nigaṇṭhā "
"ekasāṭakā. (3)"
msgstr ""
"The red class of rebirth consists of the Jain ascetics who wear one cloth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena haliddābhijāti paññattā, gihī "
"odātavasanā acelakasāvakā. (4)"
msgstr ""
"The yellow class of rebirth consists of the lay people dressed in white who "
"are disciples of the naked ascetics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena sukkābhijāti paññattā, ājīvakā "
"ājīvakiniyo. (5)"
msgstr ""
"The white class of rebirth consists of male and female <i>Ājīvaka</i> "
"ascetics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ, bhante, pūraṇena kassapena paramasukkābhijāti paññattā, nando "
"vaccho kiso saṅkicco makkhali gosālo. (6)"
msgstr ""
"And the ultimate white class of rebirth consists of Nanda Vaccha, Kisa "
"Saṅkicca, and Makkhali Gosāla."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:8.1"
msgid "Pūraṇena, bhante, kassapena imā chaḷabhijātiyo paññattā”ti."
msgstr "These are the six classes of rebirth that Pūraṇa Kassapa describes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ panānanda, pūraṇassa kassapassa sabbo loko etadabbhanujānāti imā "
"chaḷabhijātiyo paññāpetun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Ānanda, did the whole world authorize Pūraṇa Kassapa to describe these "
"six classes of rebirth?”"

msgctxt "an6.57:9.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.57:9.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, puriso daliddo assako anāḷhiko, tassa akāmakassa bilaṃ "
"olaggeyyuṃ: ‘idaṃ te, ambho purisa, maṃsañca khāditabbaṃ, mūlañca "
"anuppadātabban’ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s as if they were to force a steak on a poor, penniless person, telling "
"them they must eat it and then pay for it."

msgctxt "an6.57:9.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, ānanda, pūraṇena kassapena appaṭiññāya etesaṃ "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ imā chaḷabhijātiyo paññattā, yathā taṃ bālena abyattena "
"akhettaññunā akusalena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, Pūraṇa Kassapa has described these six classes of rebirth "
"without the consent of those ascetics and brahmins. And he has done so in a "
"foolish, incompetent, unskilled way, lacking common sense."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.385"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:10.1"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panānanda, chaḷabhijātiyo paññāpemi."
msgstr "I, however, also describe six classes of rebirth."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an6.57:10.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

msgctxt "an6.57:10.5"
msgid "“katamā cānanda, chaḷabhijātiyo?"
msgstr "“And what, Ānanda, are the six classes of rebirth?"

msgctxt "an6.57:10.6"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati."
msgstr "Someone born into a dark class gives rise to a dark result."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.7"
msgid "Idha panānanda, ekacco kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno sukkaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati."
msgstr "Someone born into a dark class gives rise to a bright result."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.8"
msgid ""
"Idha panānanda, ekacco kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ "
"abhijāyati."
msgstr ""
"Someone born into a dark class gives rise to extinguishment, which is "
"neither dark nor bright."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.9"
msgid "Idha panānanda, ekacco sukkābhijātiyo samāno kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati."
msgstr "Someone born into a bright class gives rise to a dark result."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.10"
msgid "Idha panānanda, ekacco sukkābhijātiyo samāno sukkaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati."
msgstr "Someone born into a bright class gives rise to a bright result."

msgctxt "an6.57:10.11"
msgid ""
"Idha panānanda, ekacco sukkābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ "
"abhijāyati."
msgstr ""
"Someone born into a bright class gives rise to extinguishment, which is "
"neither dark nor bright."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:11.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati?"
msgstr "And how does someone born into a dark class give rise to a dark result?"

#. VAR: venakule → veṇakule (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an6.57:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, ekacco nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā nesādakule vā "
"venakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā, dalidde appannapānabhojane "
"kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone is reborn in a low family—a family of outcastes, bamboo-"
"workers, hunters, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors—poor, with little to "
"eat or drink, where life is tough, and food and shelter are hard to find."

msgctxt "an6.57:11.3"
msgid ""
"So ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā "
"pakkhahato vā, na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa "
"mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa."
msgstr ""
"And they’re ugly, unsightly, deformed, chronically ill—one-eyed, crippled, "
"lame, or half-paralyzed. They don’t get to have food, drink, clothes, and "
"vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; or bed, house, and lighting."

msgctxt "an6.57:11.4"
msgid ""
"So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ "
"carati."
msgstr "And they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an6.57:11.5"
msgid ""
"So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ "
"caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an6.57:11.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati. (1)"
msgstr "That’s how someone born into a dark class gives rise to a dark result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:12.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno sukkaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati?"
msgstr ""
"And how does someone born into a dark class give rise to a bright result?"

msgctxt "an6.57:12.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā … pe …"
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in a low family …"

msgctxt "an6.57:12.3"
msgid "seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.57:12.4"
msgid ""
"So kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati."
msgstr "But they do good things by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an6.57:12.5"
msgid ""
"So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā, manasā sucaritaṃ "
"caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

msgctxt "an6.57:12.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno sukkaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati. (2)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how someone born into a dark class gives rise to a bright result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.386"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an6.57:13.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañcānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati?"
msgstr ""
"And how does someone born into a dark class give rise to extinguishment, "
"which is neither dark nor bright?"

msgctxt "an6.57:13.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā … pe …"
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in a low family …"

msgctxt "an6.57:13.3"
msgid "so ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.57:13.4"
msgid ""
"So kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajati."
msgstr ""
"They shave off their hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from "
"the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "an6.57:13.5"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇe, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto, satta bojjhaṅge "
"yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati."
msgstr ""
"They give up the five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. They firmly establish their mind in the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation. They truly develop the seven awakening factors. And then they "
"give rise to extinguishment, which is neither dark nor bright."

msgctxt "an6.57:13.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, ānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati. "
"(3)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how someone born in a dark class gives rise to extinguishment, which "
"is neither dark nor bright."

